      "content": "i mean, if the laws are outdated, doesn't that make any new enforcement basically just arbitrary? it feels a bit like the government is just moving the goalposts because they don't like how much influence these platforms have. wouldn't a better way be to just update the laws through congress instead of having agencies try to force this stuff through with old rules? it seems kinda risky for the economy if they just start breaking things up for no clear legal reason.",
